data.meta_description: June 30, 2001 - American guitarist and producer Chet Atkins died in Nashville aged 77. Recorded over 100 albums during his career, produced records for Perry Como, Elvis Presley, Don Gibson, Jim Reeves and Waylon Jennings. Was a major influence on George Harrison and Mark Knopfler. •• #chetatkins #thisdayinmusic #2000s #guitar #songwriter #producer #rip #restinpeace
